Tata Power Co.,  India â€™s biggest
non-state power producer, sold $450 million of subordinated
notes, according to a person familiar with the matter.  The 60-year bonds, which can be bought back by the company
after five years, were sold to yield 8.5 percent, the person
said, asking not to be identified as details are private.  Tata Power received orders for the sale, which was managed
by Deutsche Bank AG, Goldman Sachs Group Inc. and UBS AG, of
more than $3.5 billion from investors around the world, the
